{"_id":"96rJI71zlf93bFqB","name":"Rules","content":"<p><strong>Rule 1:</strong></p>\n<p>When you die, your soul becomes exposed. If it is not interfered with, you will revive in Homestead 24 hours later with only the items forged from your own soul. If your soul is tampered with, then the item created from it will contain your essense and must be unmade for you to return to sentience.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Rule 2:</strong></p>\n<p>If you read the description of a lootable item then you are holding it and examining it. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Rule 3:</strong></p>\n<p>You do not lose your level if you lose XP</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration:line-through\">If you lose XP your level remains the same however you will lose level benefits beginning when you cross the level threshold below your current level.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"text-decoration:line-through\">Level 11: 85000 XP</span><br /><span style=\"text-decoration:line-through\">Level 10: 64000 XP</span><br /><span style=\"text-decoration:line-through\">Level 9: 48000 XP</span><br /><span style=\"text-decoration:line-through\">Level 8: 34000 XP</span><br /><br /><span style=\"text-decoration:line-through\">If you are at level 10 and lose XP you will retain all level 10 features until you are below 48000 XP at which point you will still be level 10 but will only have level 9 features. The same thing will happen if you go below 34000 XP. If you begin gaining XP again, you will regain lost features in the same way. Until you return to your current level at which point leveling works as normal.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Rule 4:</strong><br />Soul forging uses souls to create items from the living world in the land of the dead.</p>\n<p>A soul forger can unmake soul forged items back into minor souls.</p>\n<p>A soul forger can infuse one soul with the essence of another.</p>\n<p>A soul forger can sever the bond of a soul forged item.<br /><br /><strong>Rule 5:</strong><br />Lesser and Greater souls<br /><br />- lesser souls are worth a fixed amount (1000 xp) and can be used to craft non-magical items.<br />- There should be around 1000 of these lesser souls available in the game.<br />- The conversion between gold and lesser souls is: Round Up((gold*10)/1000)</p>\n<p>Greater souls are worth a variable amount and can be used to craft specific magic items. <br /><br /><strong>Rule 6:</strong><br />Life Amulet: Each turn you are below max HP, gain 2d10 hit points. If you are at 0 hit points when this occurs,<span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"> take 1 point of exhaustion.</span></p>\n<p>Death <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Amulet</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">: If an effect would reduce you to 0 hit points, instead you remain at 1 HP and take 1 point of exhaustion.</span></p>\n<p>Energy <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Amulet</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">: If you have 0 spell slots, gain 1 random spell slot you have access to </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">and take 1 point of exhaustion</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">.</span></p>\n<p>Will <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Amulet</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">: You cannot fail intelligence saving throws, instead</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"> take 1 point of exhaustion.</span></p>\n<p>Earth <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Amulet</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">: You cannot fail Strength saving throws</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">, instead</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"> take 1 point of exhaustion.</span></p>\n<p>Balance <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Amulet</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">: Whenever you gain hit points, that many hit points are lost divided among the creatures within 30 feet of you. Whenever you lose hit points, that many hit points are gained divided among the creatures within 30 feet of you</span></p>\n<p>Time <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Amulet</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">: You always go first in any combat, and have 1 legendary resistance per day. Using a legendary resistance causes 1 point of exhaustion.  <br /></span></p>","folder":"l2BnOQQTdztiQFWG","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"vmPmArlBOnlDRCNW":3},"flags":{}}
